post.description:
Bulk create, update, and delete widgets for a dashboard.

All operations are performed in a single transaction.

Request body:
{
    "create": [{"name": "Widget 1", "field": "duration", "chart_type": "line"}, ...],
    "update": [{"id": 1, "name": "Updated Name"}, ...],
    "delete": [2, 3, 4]
}

Returns:
{
    "created": [...],  # List of created widgets
    "updated": [...],  # List of updated widgets
    "deleted": [...]   # List of deleted widget IDs
}

Duplicate a dashboard and all its widgets.

Creates a copy of the dashboard with all its widgets.
The new dashboard will have the same filters and widgets as the original.

Request body (optional):
{
    "name": "My Custom Name"  # Optional, defaults to "<original_name> (Copy)"
}

Returns:
    The newly created dashboard with all duplicated widgets.

post.description:
Preview widget data without saving the widget.

Accepts widget configuration and returns plot data.
Useful for previewing chart configurations before saving.

Required fields:
- dashboard: Dashboard ID (to scope data to the correct project)
- field: Field name to plot
- chart_type: Type of chart (line, bar, pie)

Optional fields:
- filters: Filters for the data (widget-level filters)
- metric: Metric ID (required when field is 'metric_evaluations.value')
- time_period: Time period for bar charts
- aggregation_function: Aggregation function for bar charts
- dashboard_filters: Filters to override dashboard filters (combined with widget filters)

parameters.name: filters_v2
parameters.description:
Advanced JSON filters using CallLogQueryFilter format (same as dashboard filters).
Supports nested AND/OR conditions, field comparisons, and related field filtering.

Example - Simple filter:
`{"field": "success", "op": "eq", "value": true}`

Example - AND conditions:
`{"operator": "and", "conditions": [{"field": "success", "op": "eq", "value": true}, {"field": "duration", "op": "gte", "value": 60}]}`

Example - OR conditions:
`{"operator": "or", "conditions": [{"field": "call_ended_reason", "op": "eq", "value": "completed"}, {"field": "call_ended_reason", "op": "eq", "value": "hangup"}]}`

Supported fields: success, duration, call_id, timestamp, created_at, call_ended_reason, customer_number, etc.
Supported operators: eq, neq, gt, gte, lt, lte, contains, startswith, in, isnull

Takes a transcript in JSON format and processes it for simulation testing,
saving the processed data to the specified scenario including embeddings and
formatted simulation description.

Request body:
    - transcript_json: List of transcript message objects with format:
        [
            {"role": "Main Agent", "content": "Hello"},
            {"role": "Testing Agent", "content": "Hi"},
            ...
        ]

Returns:
    - Scenario data with updated transcript simulation data

Updates:
    - transcript_embeddings: Embeddings for Main Agent responses
    - simulation_description: Formatted transcript description
